♪I still need fresh reasons for myself♪

23
00:01:42,590 --> 00:01:47,070
=Hilarious Family 2=

24
00:01:47,340 --> 00:01:50,260
=Episode 28=

25
00:02:07,110 --> 00:02:08,170
Slowly, slowly.

26
00:02:11,900 --> 00:02:12,960
The contest is over?

27
00:02:16,340 --> 00:02:18,980
(Quiet and Beautiful, Bright and Fancy)

28
00:02:18,990 --> 00:02:20,680
Have you found the tea leaves?

29
00:02:21,900 --> 00:02:22,840
Yes.

30
00:02:23,550 --> 00:02:24,610
What was the result?

31
00:02:25,070 --> 00:02:26,770
Can't you see? He lost.

32
00:02:29,670 --> 00:02:32,680
What... What tea won the first prize?

33
00:02:32,900 --> 00:02:34,050
Luo Zhusi's Aji Tea.

34
00:02:34,860 --> 00:02:37,770
This year's first prize

35
00:02:38,460 --> 00:02:39,520
goes to Aji Tea

36
00:02:40,860 --> 00:02:41,800
from Jinyu Tea.

37
00:02:48,620 --> 00:02:50,460
(Anning Prefecture Tea Contest)

38
00:02:54,830 --> 00:02:55,890
How come?

39
00:02:56,830 --> 00:02:58,050
Maybe I was too reckless.

40
00:02:58,990 --> 00:02:59,930
It was my fault.

41
00:03:00,070 --> 00:03:01,240
Kan, don't blame yourself.

42
00:03:01,390 --> 00:03:02,330
It's not your fault.

43
00:03:02,580 --> 00:03:04,330
I heard they had bribed the authorities.

44
00:03:04,460 --> 00:03:05,460
We didn't bribe them,

45
00:03:05,460 --> 00:03:06,400
so we lost the game.

46
00:03:11,900 --> 00:03:12,840
It's all right,

47
00:03:13,110 --> 00:03:14,050
young man.

48
00:03:14,550 --> 00:03:15,930
We're still young.

49
00:03:19,740 --> 00:03:20,680
Before we win,

50
00:03:21,140 --> 00:03:22,520
the contest will never end.

51
00:03:23,670 --> 00:03:24,960
But I made a bet with Luo Zhusi.

52
00:03:25,670 --> 00:03:27,170
We'll have to leave our residence.

53
00:03:27,620 --> 00:03:28,720
It's nothing.

54
00:03:29,350 --> 00:03:30,840
I'm fed up with living there.

55
00:03:31,510 --> 00:03:32,390
This is a good chance

56
00:03:32,390 --> 00:03:33,330
for us to travel around.

57
00:03:34,110 --> 00:03:35,090
Do you really not mind?

58
00:03:35,300 --> 00:03:36,240
No, of course.

59
00:03:36,390 --> 00:03:37,930
Come on. I'll go buy you some noodles.

60
00:03:39,110 --> 00:03:40,390
And two eggs.

61
00:03:40,390 --> 00:03:41,650
Luo Zhusi will be jealous.

62
00:03:41,790 --> 00:03:43,400
All right. I'll pay the bill.

63
00:03:44,180 --> 00:03:45,120
You've moved on?

64
00:03:47,580 --> 00:03:48,840
I'm just getting emotional.

65
00:03:49,110 --> 00:03:50,640
I'm about to cry, but they've moved on?

66
00:03:51,990 --> 00:03:52,930
Wait a minute.

67
00:03:53,950 --> 00:03:54,890
You stole zongzi, right?

68
00:03:57,500 --> 00:03:58,960
Did... Did you see that?

69
00:04:00,050 --> 00:04:01,140
Don't... Don't stare at me.

70
00:04:01,140 --> 00:04:02,300
Don't be ridiculous.

71
00:04:02,300 --> 00:04:03,560
Did you catch me in the act?

72
00:04:04,110 --> 00:04:04,950
If you didn't,

73
00:04:04,950 --> 00:04:06,090
why did you complain?

74
00:04:06,990 --> 00:04:07,960
What a psychopath.

75
00:04:09,350 --> 00:04:10,350
Oh, I'm getting excited.

76
00:04:10,350 --> 00:04:11,400
Come on. Stop over there.

77
00:04:11,830 --> 00:04:12,740
Why?

78
00:04:12,740 --> 00:04:13,700
Wait.

79
00:04:13,700 --> 00:04:14,540
I'm telling you,

80
00:04:14,540 --> 00:04:15,600
you didn't steal, then.

81
00:04:35,180 --> 00:04:39,420
(Jing Residence)

82
00:04:39,440 --> 00:04:41,450
Madam, we finally won the first prize.

83
00:04:41,910 --> 00:04:42,820
We did, at last.

84
00:04:42,820 --> 00:04:43,920
All right, all right.

85
00:04:44,110 --> 00:04:45,140
Are you a parrot?

86
00:04:45,150 --> 00:04:46,480
You've repeated it many times.

87
00:04:48,820 --> 00:04:51,400
Now, I'm relieved.

88
00:04:52,030 --> 00:04:53,710
People used to think

89
00:04:53,710 --> 00:04:55,600
this was a family of tribute tea

90
00:04:55,710 --> 00:04:56,670
because of Qin Baoyi,

91
00:04:56,670 --> 00:04:58,250
the coquettish woman.

92
00:04:58,710 --> 00:05:00,280
Now, it proves that you can also help.

93
00:05:00,550 --> 00:05:02,420
And Qin Baoyi couldn't succeed

94
00:05:02,420 --> 00:05:03,360
without Master's help.

95
00:05:03,470 --> 00:05:04,350
You don't need that.

96
00:05:04,350 --> 00:05:05,600
You've been all alone.

97
00:05:05,620 --> 00:05:07,150
Nobody has cared about you.

98
00:05:07,150 --> 00:05:08,490
- Come on.
- Only I'm...

99
00:05:08,790 --> 00:05:09,840
Stop nagging.

100
00:05:10,820 --> 00:05:11,920
At tomorrow's banquet,

101
00:05:12,500 --> 00:05:13,810
you don't nag like this.

102
00:05:15,420 --> 00:05:18,960
By then, clan relatives will come.

103
00:05:19,150 --> 00:05:21,570
Tell Aji to get ready

104
00:05:22,420 --> 00:05:23,650
for tomorrow's inauguration.

105
00:05:24,030 --> 00:05:24,940
- Ms. Luo.
- I get it.

106
00:05:24,940 --> 00:05:25,880
This is great.

107
00:05:26,260 --> 00:05:28,480
You also know we won the Tea Contest?

108
00:05:28,680 --> 00:05:29,550
No, no.

109
00:05:29,550 --> 00:05:30,720
My master is back.

110
00:05:43,110 --> 00:05:44,050
Mother.

111
00:05:44,420 --> 00:05:45,360
I'm a really bad son.

112
00:05:45,360 --> 00:05:46,900
(Jing Nanfeng, Wei Junyi's eldest son)

113
00:05:48,300 --> 00:05:49,240
My son.

114
00:05:50,420 --> 00:05:52,450
Get up now.

115
00:05:52,860 --> 00:05:54,250
Get up.

116
00:05:57,180 --> 00:05:58,570
All these years,

117
00:05:59,030 --> 00:06:00,960
where have you been?

118
00:06:01,230 --> 00:06:02,610
- Mother.
- Nanfeng.

119
00:06:03,820 --> 00:06:04,760
Nan...

120
00:06:04,990 --> 00:06:05,930
Zhusi.

121
00:06:06,620 --> 00:06:07,570
You're back.

122
00:06:08,230 --> 00:06:09,170
But we were told

123
00:06:09,710 --> 00:06:11,480
your ship was wrecked

124
00:06:11,910 --> 00:06:13,520
and nobody survived.

125
00:06:14,380 --> 00:06:15,380
Zhusi,

126
00:06:15,380 --> 00:06:17,520
am... Am I mistaken?

127
00:06:18,740 --> 00:06:19,680
No.

128
00:06:20,670 --> 00:06:21,610
Mother,

129
00:06:21,820 --> 00:06:23,060
our ship

130
00:06:23,060 --> 00:06:24,090
did sink.

131
00:06:24,380 --> 00:06:26,990
But some fishermen saved my life.

132
00:06:26,990 --> 00:06:28,890
I wandered and ended up
on Qiongzhou Island.

133
00:06:29,300 --> 00:06:30,150
In this case,

134
00:06:30,150 --> 00:06:31,710
why didn't you send back a message?

135
00:06:31,710 --> 00:06:32,650
Yeah.

136
00:06:33,060 --> 00:06:34,000
All these years,

137
00:06:34,110 --> 00:06:35,450
I... I thought you were...

138
00:06:37,670 --> 00:06:38,820
I also didn't know

139
00:06:38,820 --> 00:06:40,040
I could come back alive.

140
00:06:43,350 --> 00:06:44,650
Glad you're back.

141
00:06:45,710 --> 00:06:47,090
Glad you're back.

142
00:06:48,260 --> 00:06:49,200
Sadly,

143
00:06:50,380 --> 00:06:53,600
you didn't see your father
before he died.

144
00:06:54,030 --> 00:06:54,970
Mother,

145
00:06:55,180 --> 00:06:56,920
only after going through this

146
00:06:57,180 --> 00:06:58,120
did I realize

147
00:06:58,500 --> 00:07:00,130
I was sorry

148
00:07:00,590 --> 00:07:01,650
for you and Father.

149
00:07:02,860 --> 00:07:03,800
Don't worry.

150
00:07:04,350 --> 00:07:05,290
I know I was wrong.

151
00:07:05,940 --> 00:07:07,090
I won't do that anymore.

152
00:07:07,550 --> 00:07:08,960
As long as you're alive,

153
00:07:09,910 --> 00:07:12,040
Mother will be content.

154
00:07:13,820 --> 00:07:14,760
Mother,

155
00:07:15,180 --> 00:07:17,480
let me offer incense to Father.

156
00:07:37,460 --> 00:07:42,340
(Zuixian Restaurant)

157
00:08:03,260 --> 00:08:05,160
Didn't we have a deal?

158
00:08:06,110 --> 00:08:07,600
When I give you fifty taels a month,

159
00:08:07,820 --> 00:08:10,520
you'll live alone out there

160
00:08:10,940 --> 00:08:12,960
and never come back.

161
00:08:15,420 --> 00:08:16,360
Zhusi,

162
00:08:16,740 --> 00:08:18,210
my health condition

163
00:08:18,820 --> 00:08:19,840
has been worse and worse.

164
00:08:20,180 --> 00:08:21,130
When I was young,

165
00:08:21,740 --> 00:08:23,710
I didn't think anything could

166
00:08:23,710 --> 00:08:25,130
be compared to gambling.

167
00:08:25,690 --> 00:08:26,550
For gambling,

168
00:08:26,550 --> 00:08:27,720
I could abandon anything.

169
00:08:28,350 --> 00:08:29,450
But one day,

170
00:08:30,060 --> 00:08:31,890
I witnessed the death of a friend.

171
00:08:32,830 --> 00:08:34,330
When he was dying,

172
00:08:35,260 --> 00:08:36,950
there was nobody

173
00:08:36,950 --> 00:08:37,890
around him.

174
00:08:38,110 --> 00:08:40,690
At that time, I realized

175
00:08:41,310 --> 00:08:43,120
I still needed a home.

176
00:08:46,190 --> 00:08:49,120
Do you think I'll believe that?

177
00:08:50,230 --> 00:08:51,760
I don't care.

178
00:08:52,070 --> 00:08:53,120
When I'm back here,

179
00:08:53,500 --> 00:08:55,210
I'll tell you three things.

180
00:08:55,620 --> 00:08:56,560
First,

181
00:08:57,190 --> 00:08:58,600
I won't tell anyone

182
00:08:58,900 --> 00:09:00,570
you didn't want me to come back.

183
00:09:00,740 --> 00:09:01,680
Second,

184
00:09:01,860 --> 00:09:03,190
I won't compete with you

185
00:09:03,190 --> 00:09:04,990
for the position of the chief manager.

186
00:09:04,990 --> 00:09:05,930
Third...

187
00:09:07,660 --> 00:09:08,600
I will keep

188
00:09:09,500 --> 00:09:10,440
your secret

189
00:09:10,900 --> 00:09:12,290
about Luo Aji.

190
00:09:15,620 --> 00:09:16,560
Well,

191
00:09:17,990 --> 00:09:20,120
I have three things to say, too.

192
00:09:21,540 --> 00:09:22,480
First,

193
00:09:23,310 --> 00:09:25,210
it's not that I didn't want you back,

194
00:09:25,470 --> 00:09:26,880
but because you and I

195
00:09:27,350 --> 00:09:28,480
had a deal.

196
00:09:29,710 --> 00:09:30,650
Second,

197
00:09:31,710 --> 00:09:33,290
it's not that you won't compete

198
00:09:33,660 --> 00:09:34,860
for that position.

199
00:09:34,860 --> 00:09:37,570
You're just not good enough.

200
00:09:38,230 --> 00:09:39,230
Third,

201
00:09:39,230 --> 00:09:40,690
there's no secret about Aji.

202
00:09:41,230 --> 00:09:42,290
I also hope

203
00:09:42,780 --> 00:09:44,330
you won't think you can threaten me

204
00:09:44,660 --> 00:09:46,170
with all this.

205
00:09:47,900 --> 00:09:48,840
Zhusi,

206
00:09:53,350 --> 00:09:54,450
don't get me wrong.

207
00:09:54,990 --> 00:09:56,760
I know it's of no use to say anything.

208
00:09:57,380 --> 00:09:58,320
But anyway,

209
00:09:58,590 --> 00:09:59,530
as time goes by,

210
00:10:00,110 --> 00:10:01,050
you will know.

211
00:10:14,310 --> 00:10:15,250
Mingzhen.

212
00:10:15,950 --> 00:10:17,020
Perfect timing.

213
00:10:17,020 --> 00:10:18,230
Pack the teacups in Yanxia Chamber

214
00:10:18,230 --> 00:10:19,170
and I'll take them away.

215
00:10:19,740 --> 00:10:20,680
Here.

216
00:10:21,780 --> 00:10:23,690
(Intoxicating Spring)
Where are you going?

217
00:10:24,500 --> 00:10:25,440
I have to leave here.

218
00:10:25,990 --> 00:10:26,930
Take care of Grandmother.

219
00:10:27,660 --> 00:10:28,760
You're really leaving?

220
00:10:29,990 --> 00:10:30,930
Just go.

221
00:10:33,590 --> 00:10:34,530
Zhenzhu.

222
00:10:35,660 --> 00:10:36,600
Zhenzhu.

223
00:10:37,660 --> 00:10:38,960
I washed some fruit for you.

224
00:10:39,190 --> 00:10:40,130
I don't want that.

225
00:10:40,620 --> 00:10:41,560
Zhenzhu,

226
00:10:41,900 --> 00:10:42,960
don't ignore Father.

227
00:10:45,260 --> 00:10:47,530
Uncle, what's wrong with Zhenzhu?

228
00:10:48,190 --> 00:10:49,130
Nothing.

229
00:10:49,660 --> 00:10:51,290
I did many foolish things before.

230
00:10:51,900 --> 00:10:52,840
It's normal

231
00:10:53,260 --> 00:10:54,200
that she ignores me.

232
00:10:55,590 --> 00:10:57,330
It's all right. Glad you're back.

233
00:10:59,470 --> 00:11:01,110
I heard you did very well

234
00:11:01,110 --> 00:11:02,050
in the Tea Contest.

235
00:11:02,190 --> 00:11:03,480
I feel happy for you.

236
00:11:05,230 --> 00:11:06,240
I lost, anyway.

237
00:11:06,500 --> 00:11:07,930
I made a bet with Luo Zhusi.

238
00:11:08,070 --> 00:11:09,210
I have to leave home now.

239
00:11:09,470 --> 00:11:10,410
Leave?

240
00:11:10,990 --> 00:11:11,900
Even a family

241
00:11:11,900 --> 00:11:13,050
shouldn't have had that bet.

242
00:11:14,070 --> 00:11:15,740
Forget it. What's gone is gone.

243
00:11:15,740 --> 00:11:17,000
This is ridiculous.

244
00:11:17,310 --> 00:11:18,160
You won't go anywhere.

245
00:11:18,170 --> 00:11:19,010
I'll talk to them.

246
00:11:20,230 --> 00:11:21,620
- Take this.
- But Uncle...

247
00:11:21,620 --> 00:11:22,500
I will be back.

248
00:11:22,500 --> 00:11:23,370
Don't go anywhere.

249
00:11:23,380 --> 00:11:24,230
No need, Uncle.

250
00:11:24,230 --> 00:11:25,170
Uncle.

251
00:11:32,900 --> 00:11:33,860
Today, I saw how Zhenzhu

252
00:11:33,860 --> 00:11:34,810
treated Uncle.

253
00:11:35,020 --> 00:11:36,360
I think it's really hard for him.

254
00:11:37,660 --> 00:11:39,330
But I do understand Zhenzhu.

255
00:11:39,740 --> 00:11:41,380
Uncle did so many bad things to her.

256
00:11:41,380 --> 00:11:42,760
She wouldn't just forgive him.

257
00:11:42,950 --> 00:11:44,260
I think Uncle has changed a lot

258
00:11:44,260 --> 00:11:45,290
when he's back here.

259
00:11:46,430 --> 00:11:48,000
Looks like one will figure out a lot

260
00:11:48,350 --> 00:11:49,570
after he's nearly dead.

261
00:11:50,590 --> 00:11:52,130
We're a family, after all.

262
00:11:52,540 --> 00:11:53,930
Family members forgive each other.

263
00:11:54,310 --> 00:11:56,000
That depends.

264
00:11:56,950 --> 00:11:58,230
A gambler

265
00:11:58,230 --> 00:11:59,880
can hardly give up gambling.

266
00:12:00,500 --> 00:12:01,690
We should be careful, anyway.

267
00:12:04,760 --> 00:12:05,810
When I think

268
00:12:06,020 --> 00:12:07,330
we're moving out tomorrow,

269
00:12:07,710 --> 00:12:08,650
I feel quite reluctant.

270
00:12:11,110 --> 00:12:12,360
How about I move out alone?

271
00:12:12,590 --> 00:12:13,530
You can stay here.

272
00:12:14,950 --> 00:12:15,900
Sounds good.

273
00:12:15,900 --> 00:12:16,880
I won't get packed, then.

274
00:12:22,660 --> 00:12:23,600
You're angry?

275
00:12:24,620 --> 00:12:25,880
I was just kidding.

276
00:12:26,660 --> 00:12:27,900
Don't you know that saying?

277
00:12:27,900 --> 00:12:29,960
"A woman always follows her husband.

278
00:12:30,230 --> 00:12:31,360
What if Kan is her husband?

279
00:12:31,990 --> 00:12:32,930
She sticks to him."

280
00:12:33,940 --> 00:12:34,860
I've got a plan.

281
00:12:35,580 --> 00:12:36,900
After we move out,

282
00:12:37,100 --> 00:12:38,060
I'll rent a house

283
00:12:38,060 --> 00:12:39,020
with a storefront.

284
00:12:39,500 --> 00:12:40,660
We sell tea and live there.

285
00:12:40,980 --> 00:12:42,180
What about Anping Bridge Shop?

286
00:12:43,140 --> 00:12:44,300
We lost, right?

287
00:12:45,100 --> 00:12:46,660
So, we will give it back

288
00:12:47,500 --> 00:12:48,660
to Jinyu Tea.

289
00:12:49,980 --> 00:12:51,660
If I remember correctly,

